This paper is about keyphrase generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The proposed model is a recurrent-generative model, which is a common type of NLP model. The evaluation metrics are also tailored towards variable-number generation, which is a specific aspect of NLP evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
